docs.lead_paragraph: As recently as five years ago, pediatricians hesitated to bleed a baby for full diagnostic studies because the relatively large quantities of blood required involved dangers to the infant.

headline.main: MICROCHEMISTRY AIDS SICK BABIES; A Pinprick Provides Enough Blood for Full Tests

docs.abstract: microchemical method of taking very small amts of blood from infants for accurate diagnostic tests described; Dr K Engel comments
